  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are various legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI (1991)\n- Landmark case involving international bank fraud\n- Significant prosecution of widespread money laundering activities\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Led to significant regulatory reforms\n\n3. United States v. Martin Act\n- New York state law allowing aggressive prosecution of financial crimes\n- Broad investigative powers for financial fraud cases\n\n4. Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act (RICO)\n- Allows prosecution of organized financial criminal enterprises\n- Enables seizure of assets connected to illegal activities\n\n5. Basel Committee recommendations\n- International standards for anti-money laundering procedures\n- Established global framework for detecting financial crimes\n\nThese precedents demonstrate evolving legal approaches to combating money laundering through enhanced investigation techniques, international cooperation, and comprehensive financial regulations.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal precedents?",
